{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":16513,"name":"Rico Decho","username":"rico.decho","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rico.decho/{size}/239_2.png","created_at":"2017-03-10T07:47:15.046Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIf you want pure execution performance, the best scripting language I know is Cling.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt’s an interactive C++ interpreter, based on LLVM.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBasically it compiles C++ code interactively within the host application.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat’s much more efficient than the DLL compilation hacks (RCCpp, etc)…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd the best part of that is that once your scripts run fine in the C++ interpreter, you can add them to you C++ application build files \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/grinning.png?v=5\" title=\":grinning:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":grinning:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAwesome !\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e(reposted)\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-03-10T07:47:15.046Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":199,"reads":94,"readers_count":93,"score":1058.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"Rico Decho","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":682,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":16516,"name":"","username":"TheSHEEEP","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/thesheeep/{size}/74_2.png","created_at":"2017-03-10T08:57:21.946Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eInteresting. Not suited for all use cases (I don’t think you want to expose scripters to C++ syntax and pitfalls, for example), but for where it can be used, that’s pretty neat.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-03-10T08:57:21.946Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":94,"readers_count":93,"score":18.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":513,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":16518,"name":"","username":"sabotage3d","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/sabotage3d/{size}/87_2.png","created_at":"2017-03-10T11:45:18.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eLooks really cool. Thanks for sharing. Do you know if you can link it to external libraries?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-03-10T11:45:18.000Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":92,"readers_count":91,"score":23.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":151,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":16519,"name":"Rico Decho","username":"rico.decho","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rico.decho/{size}/239_2.png","created_at":"2017-03-10T12:09:18.615Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eBasically, it’s just made to be embedded in a host application and directly use its declared types and functions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo I’ve absolutely no idea what should be done to make it work with loaded DLLs for instance.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-03-10T12:09:18.615Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":88,"readers_count":87,"score":17.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"Rico Decho","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"sabotage3d","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/sabotage3d/{size}/87_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":682,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":16520,"name":"","username":"godan","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png","created_at":"2017-03-10T12:55:50.723Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThis looks excellent!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-03-10T12:55:50.723Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":87,"readers_count":86,"score":27.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":134,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":20464,"name":"hicup","username":"hicup_82017","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/hicup_82017/{size}/762_2.png","created_at":"2017-08-27T14:18:17.131Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello,\u003cbr\u003e\nAny of you tried this?\u003cbr\u003e\nI am just into Urho3d and interested to learn c++ a bit better. I only work with embedded C all the time. So this would allow me to bypass LUA learning and enhance my c++ skill set as well.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks in advance \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-08-27T14:18:17.131Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":75,"readers_count":74,"score":30.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"hicup","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":808,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":20465,"name":"","username":"JTippetts","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jtippetts/{size}/357_2.png","created_at":"2017-08-27T14:49:00.822Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThere’s no requirement of using Lua. Just use C++. What this thread is describing is a “different way” of using C++, that’s all. You’ve always been able to use C++ in the traditional fashion with Urho3D, as that is the language the engine itself is written in.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-08-27T14:49:00.822Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":71,"readers_count":70,"score":34.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"hicup_82017","name":"hicup","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/hicup_82017/{size}/762_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":30,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":20550,"name":"hicup","username":"hicup_82017","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/hicup_82017/{size}/762_2.png","created_at":"2017-08-31T15:20:34.074Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi JTippetts,\u003cbr\u003e\nIn a sense your suggestion actually makes more sense for a newbie like me.\u003cbr\u003e\nAll I want to do is, learn and design a simple game. Since you guys already made whole Urho3D as a library. My game code compile time should be very less and worrying for it doesn’t make sense now.\u003cbr\u003e\nUpdate: Able to complete reading some of the sample programs in C++ only \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-08-31T15:21:11.235Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":65,"readers_count":64,"score":13.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"hicup","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"JTippetts","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jtippetts/{size}/357_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":808,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":29672,"name":"","username":"1vanK","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/1vank/{size}/768_2.png","created_at":"2019-05-12T09:07:20.807Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://chaiscript.com/\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://chaiscript.com/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-05-12T09:07:20.807Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":43,"readers_count":42,"score":88.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://chaiscript.com/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"ChaiScript - Easy to use scripting for C++.","clicks":6}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":263,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":29674,"name":"Leith Ketchell","username":"Leith","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/leith/{size}/2384_2.png","created_at":"2019-05-12T09:47:47.510Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWell, if we’re going to do scripting, we might as well go the whole hog, and deal with runtime compilation of c++ sourcecode - inside our runtime application. Let’s have our cake, and eat it too.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-05-12T09:47:47.510Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":44,"readers_count":43,"score":18.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"Leith Ketchell","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"suspended user","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1098,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":29677,"name":"","username":"elix22","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/elix22/{size}/1437_2.png","created_at":"2019-05-12T14:15:16.124Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe only problem ChaiScript  is that performance is very bad\u003cbr\u003e\nSee entry 48 in the Results table .\u003c/p\u003e\u003caside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://github.com/r-lyeh-archived/scriptorium\"\u003e\n  \u003cheader class=\"source\"\u003e\n      \u003cimg src=\"https://github.githubassets.com/favicons/favicon.svg\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\"\u003e\n\n      \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/r-lyeh-archived/scriptorium\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003eGitHub\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/header\u003e\n\n  \u003carticle class=\"onebox-body\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/345;\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://opengraph.githubassets.com/1f3c17abfa54f11446740b213d735d7c94c4fb2ec2848236d2189cf1cf60f38c/r-lyeh-archived/scriptorium\" class=\"thumbnail\" width=\"690\" height=\"345\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/r-lyeh-archived/scriptorium\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003eGitHub - r-lyeh-archived/scriptorium: Game Scripting Languages benchmarked\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n  \u003cp\u003e:scroll: Game Scripting Languages benchmarked. Contribute to r-lyeh-archived/scriptorium development by creating an account on GitHub.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n  \u003c/article\u003e\n\n  \u003cdiv class=\"onebox-metadata\"\u003e\n    \n    \n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \u003cdiv style=\"clear: both\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI agree with Leith ,   Runtime Compiled C++   is the only way to go .\u003cbr\u003e\nSomeone actually implemented such a thing\u003cbr\u003e\nI might surprise  with my own implementation in the future \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=10\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003caside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"318\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/pablo/40/1032_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/runtime-compiled-c-in-urho3d-aka-scripting-in-c/318\"\u003eRuntime-compiled C++ in Urho3D aka \"Scripting in C++\"\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca class=\"badge-wrapper  bullet\" href=\"/c/showcase/code-exchange/13\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"badge-category-parent-bg\" style=\"background-color: #F1592A;\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"badge-category-bg\" style=\"background-color: #231F20;\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category clear-badge\" title=\"Share your helpful Urho3D code snippets, samples and tutorials here.\"\u003eCode Exchange\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cblockquote\u003e\n    I’ve been working in this a few weeks in my spare time after work. I took the idea of using C++ as a scripting language from \u003ca href=\"http://molecularmusings.wordpress.com/2013/08/27/using-runtime-compiled-c-code-as-a-scripting-language/\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003ehttp://molecularmusings.wordpress.com/2013/08/27/using-runtime-compiled-c-code-as-a-scripting-language/\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"http://runtimecompiledcplusplus.blogspot.com\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003ehttp://runtimecompiledcplusplus.blogspot.com\u003c/a\u003e. This is technically called “Runtime-compiled C++”, which I’ll call RCCpp from now on. \nObviously, C++ is not a real scripting language, nor it tends to be. The main goal is to shrink iterations’ time while having a quick …\n  \u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-05-12T14:15:16.124Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":10,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":44,"readers_count":43,"score":33.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/r-lyeh-archived/scriptorium","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - r-lyeh-archived/scriptorium: Game Scripting Languages benchmarked","clicks":5},{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/runtime-compiled-c-in-urho3d-aka-scripting-in-c/318","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Runtime-compiled C++ in Urho3D aka \"Scripting in C++\"","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"1vanK","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/1vank/{size}/768_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":809,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":29678,"name":"","username":"S.L.C","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/s.l.c/{size}/1016_2.png","created_at":"2019-05-12T20:58:19.431Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThere is one thing that i don’t understand from this request. Which is that you don’t get anything in return.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe reason scripting is implemented in something is to simplify the entire application and allow for quick prototyping. You try something in the script. And as it grows, you look at the parts that can be moved to native code and you do that.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWith this approach, you don’t simplify anything. You are already programming in C++. In fact, you are complicating the whole process by such a degree. That any new person that wants to try out the application itself will eventually get lost in the details and rules of the implementation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis isn’t the purpose of a scripting language. And if performance is your argument (JIT). Again, this isn’t the purpose of a scripting language. You move performance critical code to native code and expose it.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-05-12T20:58:19.431Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":41,"readers_count":40,"score":13.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":180,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":29681,"name":"","username":"1vanK","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/1vank/{size}/768_2.png","created_at":"2019-05-13T03:35:52.417Z","cooked":"\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe reason scripting is implemented in something is to simplify the entire application and allow for quick prototyping.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eReason of scripting also is user’s mods and execute code from text form (triggers in levels or console commads).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWith this approach, you don’t simplify anything. You are already programming in C++.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is subjective. For me personally, C ++ is much easier than lua or angel script because I use it more often. For example idTech use c-like language for scripting.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd as it grows, you look at the parts that can be moved to native code and you do that.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is simpler when the script is already C++ code.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd if performance is your argument (JIT). Again, this isn’t the purpose of a scripting language.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt is true.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://fabiensanglard.net/doom3/interviews.php#qvm\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://fabiensanglard.net/doom3/interviews.php#qvm\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEDIT:\u003cbr\u003e\nI like quake 3 approach. \u003ca href=\"http://fabiensanglard.net/quake3/qvm.php\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://fabiensanglard.net/quake3/qvm.php\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003eOverall the VM system is very versatile since a Virtual Machine is capable of running:\n* Interpreted bytecode\n* Bytecode compiled to x86 instructions\n* Code compiled as a Windows DLL\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo if you need perfomance, you can just compile same code to native dll\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":14,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-05-13T04:00:52.577Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":13,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":7,"reads":43,"readers_count":42,"score":43.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":2880,"topic_slug":"c-as-the-scripting-language","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://fabiensanglard.net/quake3/qvm.php","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Quake 3 Source